"Zhao G., Hörmann G., Fohrer N., Zhang Z., Zhai J.","Streamflow trends and climate variability impacts in Poyang Lake basin, China",2010,"Water Resources Management","24","4",,"689","706",,,10.1007/s11269-009-9465-7,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77349086365&partnerID=40&md5=be8ce03c15305405a96e291e4ecb4c0d","Ecology Centre, Department of Hydrology and Water Resources Management, Kiel University, Kiel 24118, Germany; Jiangsu Key Laboratory of Forestry Ecological Engineering, Nanjing Forestry University, Nanjing 210037, China; Nanjing Institute of Geography and Limnology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Nanjing 210008, China","Zhao, G., Ecology Centre, Department of Hydrology and Water Resources Management, Kiel University, Kiel 24118, Germany; Hörmann, G., Ecology Centre, Department of Hydrology and Water Resources Management, Kiel University, Kiel 24118, Germany; Fohrer, N., Ecology Centre, Department of Hydrology and Water Resources Management, Kiel University, Kiel 24118, Germany; Zhang, Z., Jiangsu Key Laboratory of Forestry Ecological Engineering, Nanjing Forestry University, Nanjing 210037, China; Zhai, J., Nanjing Institute of Geography and Limnology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Nanjing 210008, China","Under the background of global warming, does the effect of the rising global surface temperature accelerate the hydrological cycle? To address this issue, we use the hydro-climatic data from five sub-basins in Poyang Lake basin in the southeast China over the past 50 years, to investigate the annual and seasonal trends of streamflow and the correlations between streamflow and climatic variables. The Theil-Sen Approach and the non-parametric Mann-Kendall test are applied to identify the trends in the annual and seasonal streamflow, precipitation and evapotranspiration series. It was found that annual and seasonal streamflow of all the stations had increasing trends except Lijiadu station in wet season. Only 37.5% hydro-stations in annual streamflow increased significantly, while most stations increased at 95% significance level in dry season. Trends in annual and seasonal precipitation during the whole period were generally not as significant as those in evapotranspiration. The correlations between streamflow and climate variables (precipitation and evapotranspiration) were detected by the Pearson's test. The results showed that streamflow in the Poyang Lake basin are more sensitive to changes in precipitation than potential evapotranspiration. © Springer Science+Business Media B.V. 2009.","Correlation; Evapotranspiration; Poyang Lake basin; Precipitation; Streamflow trends","Basin precipitation; Climate variability; Climate variables; Climatic data; Climatic variables; Dry seasons; Global surface temperature; Hydrological cycles; Mann-Kendall test; Non-parametric; Potential evapotranspiration; Poyang Lake; Poyang Lake basin; Precipitation; Seasonal precipitations; Seasonal trends; Subbasins; Wet season; Climatology; Evapotranspiration; Global warming; Lakes; Water supply; Stream flow; climate variation; correlation; evapotranspiration; hypothesis testing; precipitation (climatology); streamflow; trend analysis; China; Jiangxi; Poyang Lake",,,,,,"Allen, R.G., Pereira, L.S., Raes, D., Smith, M., Crop Evapotranspiration: Guidelines for Computing Crop Water Requirements (1998), FAO, Rome, United Nations Food and Agriculture Origanization, Irrigation and Drainage paper No. 56Aziz, O.I.A., Burn, D.H., Trends and variability in the hydrological regime of the Mackenzie River basin (2006) J Hydrol (Amst), 319, pp. 282-294. , doi:10.1016/j.jhydrol.2005.06.039; (2008) Climate Change and Water, p. 210. , Bates B.C., Kundzewicz ZW, Wu S, Palutikof JP (eds), Technical Paper of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, IPCC Secretariat, Geneva; http://www.jxsl.gov.cn/article.jsp?articleid=1815, Bureau of Rurual Hydropower and Electrification in Jiangxi Province (BRHEJX) (2006), Cited 10 Aug 2008Burn, D.H., Hag El